<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-08-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-08-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="515" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d515">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Loomis</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Newel</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-08-13"><hi rend="italic">August 13,
                                1903</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 379.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department transmits herewith a
                            printed copy of The Hague protocols.<note n="a" xml:id="d515fna">Printed
                                in <ref target="frus1903#pg_439">Foreign Relations, 1903, pp.
                                    439</ref>, <ref target="frus1903#pg_477">477</ref>, <ref target="frus1903#pg_611">611</ref>, and <ref target="frus1903#pg_804">804</ref>.</note> Certified copies are
                            on the way from Venezuela and will be forwarded to you as soon as
                            received.</p>
                        <p>The arbitrators have not yet been named. As soon as they are named you
                            will furnish, on behalf of Venezuela, to the International Bureau, a
                            copy of these protocols, with the request that the proper steps be taken
                            for the installation of the court. As soon as the Department is advised
                            of the appointment of the arbitrators, it will cable you their names, on
                            receipt of which you will carry out this instruction.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Francis B. Loomis</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>